  "target_response": {
    "text": "Yes, that's realistic, and it shouldn't cost you your training. Dropping 4 kg in ten weeks is about 0.4 kg per week — a gentle rate that a moderate calorie deficit covers without leaving you underfuelled for sessions. The playbook: keep protein high, keep your strength work and running exactly as planned, take most of the deficit from snacks and drinks rather than from the meals around training, and judge progress by the weekly average of morning weigh-ins instead of any single reading. Expect the first week to move a little faster from water, then settle into the steady rate. And if sessions start feeling flat or your sleep degrades, ease the deficit slightly — arriving at the trip 3 kg lighter and feeling strong beats 4 kg and run-down every time.",
